def: The quality or state of being slack.
One who makes, or is authorized to make, an excuse; anapologist. [Obs.] Hume.
Loss or want of reputation; ill character; disesteem;discredit.At the beginning of the eighteenth century astrology fell intogeneral disrepute. Sir W. Scott.
The quality or state of being niggard; meanness in giving orspending; parsimony; stinginess.Niggardliness is not good husbandry. Addison.

To lay under an interdict; to cut off from the enjoyment ofreligious privileges, as a city, a church, an individual.An archbishop may not only excommunicate and interdict hissuffragans, but his vicar general may do the same. Ayliffe.
The north wind; -- usually a personification.
